<br>
As a frequent Naggy raider in need of the elusive red scale for my epic, I enjoyed attending the raids run my guilds w some higher level dragon raiding experience.  These guilds ran efficient, effective raids and by doing so taught the low level raider in attendance quite a bit about raiding on a larger scale.  I also do not attend raids where I dont agree w the loot policies - specifically claiming of more than one item on a raid not counting duplicates - and those older guilds that I raided w were not doing this.  However I do understand that some of these guilds might have been exploiting the loot drops.<br>
<br>
I have also attended the raids run by some of the younger guilds and feel that they, for the most part, are a great learning experience for both the raid leaders and those in attendance.  It might take a little longer to drop the dragons and there might be a few more corpses on the ground at the end of the battle, but I have yet to attend a Naggy raid w a guild I would not join for a second Naggy raid.<br>
<br>
With the new requirements to lead a Naggy raid, what guilds will still be able to run a Naggy raid?  I dont imagine the same guilds will be interested in running these raids month after month.  As you know, leadin raids is a very taxing experience to most.  I am certainly not saying that the smaller younger guilds are not capable of running excellent dragon raids.  I personally enjoyed the mix of young and old guilds we had w the previous requirements.  As I said, the more knowledgable guilds running Naggy raids help to educate younger raiders.  The more knowledgable the raiders on our server, the stronger our server becomes.  <br>
<br>
My fears...that a lack of guilds able to meet the requirements will cause these dragons to become FCFS.  I know that many of you think this would work well at the current state of our server.  I need the red scale to complete my epic but dont want to be camped in Sol B for the rest of my days watching for someone leading a raid - then hoping I get chosen to attend.  I enjoy the use of the sign ups where raiders can chose to attend or not depending on the time/date/loot rules.  At the same time, speaking as a frquent raid leader, it is nice to be able to pick your raiders from a posted list, helping to insure you have the strenght of raid before moving to the raiding location.<br>
<br>
I realize that there are dragons other than Naggy that drop the scale that I need.  I certainly havent been level 52 for years as have some bards.  Hanging at 52 has some advantanges...I never have to worry about gettin a rez and am always available for the death touch on a raid.  I would also like to end this post by saying that I trust the wisdom of Twiggie and the other mods and will follow any rules they implement.<br>
<br>
Liseut, FLYING bard of 52 songs<br>
